00:00:45,863 --> 00:00:49,825
# With the lights out
its less dangerous

3
00:00:50,330 --> 00:00:55,927
Home to grunge, teen spirit and
the kings of alternative rock, Nirvana.

4
00:00:55,970 --> 00:00:58,139
# I feel stupid and contagious

5
00:00:58,236 --> 00:00:59,991
# Here we are now

6
00:01:00,074 --> 00:01:02,148
# Entertain us

7
00:01:02,258 --> 00:01:03,928
# A mulatto

8
00:01:03,963 --> 00:01:06,693
The band that brought the sound
of the American underground

9
00:01:06,768 --> 00:01:07,947
to a mass audience.

10
00:01:08,137 --> 00:01:11,939
The moment they took the stage
it was like hysteria, like Beatlemania.

11
00:01:12,101 --> 00:01:14,477
People crying and screaming and...

12
00:01:14,554 --> 00:01:16,303
The hair at the back
of my neck went up.

13
00:01:17,484 --> 00:01:20,964
In Kurt Cobain, Nirvana
had an artist of rare power

14
00:01:21,091 --> 00:01:23,518
who gave a voice
to a generation.

15
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:27,552
Every time he touched the guitar
it was beautiful.

16
00:01:27,597 --> 00:01:29,096
Every single time.

17
00:01:29,452 --> 00:01:34,494
He was amazing. He really had something
that I've never seen in anyone else.

18
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:37,335
Nirvana's success had put
Seattle on the map.

19
00:01:37,603 --> 00:01:41,184
Now, even the band that had laid
the foundations of alternative rock

20
00:01:41,268 --> 00:01:42,582
descended on the city,

21
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:43,765
R.E.M.

22
00:01:43,865 --> 00:01:46,820
<i>Hi, this is Mike Milles of REM
and you're listening to KC...</i>

23
00:01:46,947 --> 00:01:49,402
# That's me in the corner

24
